Step 1: Project Architecture & Navigation Setup
  
•	Create a consistent navigation system across all pages using a <header> and <nav> block.
•	Establish a file naming convention: 2a.html (Home), 2b.html (Registration), and 2c.html through 2e.html (Event Details).
  
Step 2: Developing the Home Page (2a.html)
  
•	Hero Section: Create a central landing area with a "Call to Action" button to encourage registration.
•	Event Gallery: Implement a grid layout (event-grid) using clickable cards. Each card contains an image, a title, and an overlay effect that links to specific event detail pages
  
Step 3: Creating the Registration Interface (2b.html)
  
•	Build a student registration form using the <form> tag.
•	Include essential input fields: text for Name and Register Number, and a <select> dropdown menu to allow students to choose between specific events (Coding, Expo, or Workshop).
•	Set the form action to pay.html to simulate a transition to a payment gateway.
  
Step 4: Designing Event Detail Pages (2c.html, 2d.html, 2e.html)
  
•	Workshops (2c.html): Focus on a hands-on learning description with a large featured image.
•	Coding Contest (2d.html): Create an info-list section highlighting the prize pool, venue, and technical requirements.
•	Project Expo (2e.html): Design a layout focused on innovation and exhibition details, using a distinct green color scheme for the registration button to differentiate the section.
  
Step 5: Implementing CSS Styling
  
•	External Styling: Link a global stylesheet (maha.css) to maintain visual consistency (typography, container widths, and button styles).
•	Internal Styling: Use page-specific <style> tags to handle unique layouts, such as the detail-box for event information and the overlay for gallery images.
•	Image Integration: Use high-resolution external image URLs via Unsplash to represent the technical nature of the events.
  
Step 6: Interlinking and Validation
  
•	Ensure "Back to Home" links are present on all sub-pages for easy navigation.
•	Validate form fields using the required attribute to ensure data integrity during registration.
